New Records: Namibia achieved a victory in the super over as the scores ended up in a tie after the end of two innings.
Key Match Events: David Wiese shines with both bat and ball for his team and takes them over the line.
Ruben Trumplemann and Ben Shikongo leading their attack.
Mehran Khan bowled a brilliant spell and picked up three wickets.
Naseem Khushi plays on the ball back onto the stumps.
Wiese bowls in a brilliant yorker and Khushi has no answer to hit and it is a dot ball.
Two runs from the first ball as the Maqsood plays the ball towards the long off fielder.
The Namibian captain showcases brilliance as he digs a yorker and guides it towards the third man region for a four.
The Namibian captain hits a four and the super over is turning out to be huge for Namibia.
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia impressed with their performance in the last two ICC T20 World Cup editions.
Oman are a competitive side too having impressed in the ACC T20 Premier Cup and both teams will look to start their campaign with a win.

The recent promotion of Naseem Khushi at the top of the order has given them added boost and the batter has given them solid starts allowing the middle order to ease their way a little bit into the innings.
Post-Match Reflections: David Wiese shines with both bat and ball for his team and takes them over the line.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The ICC T20 World Cup 2024 has commenced with some exciting cricket actions.
Both the opening games have been nail-biters with solid competition between the participant teams.
